    "For comparison also shown are the 0.5-2 keV number counts determined by Hasinger et al.",
    "(2005, black solid line) using ROSAT, XMM-Newton and Chandra surveys.",
    "The red shaded region and red dashed curve are the 0.5-2 keV number counts estimated from Chandra extra-galactic survey fields (Georgakakis et al. 2008).",
    "The extent of the red shaded region at fixed flux corresponds to the 1σ uncertainty.",
    "For fluxes brighter than f X (0.5-2 keV) ≈ 10 -12 erg s -1 cm -2 the red dashed curve is an extrapolation of the best-fit double power determined by Georgakakis et al. (2008)."
